Government can set an employment rate/tax benefit ratio for corporates. The more they will give employment more tax benefits they will have. 
Employment rate for last 5 years means if there was an employment of 5% additional workforce there will be a 5% decrease in tax rate for that year. 
For eg. If  A company adds 5% more workforce and was paying 30% taxes to government then now as it had added 5% workforce it should pay 25% but if in the next year it only adds 3% additional workforce compared to this year then the tax paid shall be 27 % for that year. So basically itтАЩs a discount on the tax slab for giving more employment.

This is the easiest topic to attract attention of young educated, uneducated or semi educated people in our country. These presenters simply do not have any common-sense logic to support to expect every young person to get a job of choice and liking. It never was like that ever in the history of the world. The only difference these days is heightened aspirations irrespective of qualification boosted by socialistic unmerited notion of equity facilitated by unfettered access to information and misinformation. 
Look around the world anywhere and you will find the same pyramid where those at the peak have disproportionately high share of success, fame and wealth. The same gradually reduces for those as we progressively come down the pyramid which is most crowded in the bottom layers. It is no different in so called developed nations as far as pattern of distribution of wealth and opportunity goes. As far as employment is concerned there are plenty of opportunities of employment starting at the lower end of the agriculture to the top of the corporate world. 
Problem is most of us do not want what is easily within reach even if we deserved it. We desire which is difficult to reach or perhaps impossible to reach. This desire is at the root of this dissatisfaction, often extreme and irrational. The pyramid is the natural phenomenon which always existed. So, the dissatisfaction is unlikely to reduce, but those who want to find work will definitely find work if they are flexible and practical. These discussions about unemployment would only fan passions and nothing more. Yes that may overturn regimes but would not change reality on the whole.

Many global companies have already confirmed educational certificates are not a manadste to work with them they want to hire right talent.


I hope this atleast throws some light on the details passed.

Dhruv Rathee is a Genius

An Indian should take  to his/her heart and head only the last part of the video regarding improving oneself in life and rest one should see the ground reality and not what Dhruv or any Politician is telling you about. Dont be pro Government or so anti government that you don't see anything at all. Have a neutral view for anything only then you might be able to see the REAL TRUTH. 
In my opinion this has to be the worst video I have watched by Dhruv Rathee. I have massive respect for the educational content he had been creating before he just started ranting about the Government left and right with just giving one sided story. If Dhruv is telling us the bad side of the current Government, give us the other side too. Give us the opposition side too. The good the opposition has done and what are the bad things about them too. By just keeping one sided view he is earning out pied piper of the people. Victimizing the opposition is not going to solve anything. Being viral and sharing real information is one thing and being viral and sharing one sided information that too for a well respected senior person (Internationally respected too) just because you are opposing him is another thing. Have some respect for the time he has spent for the betterment. 
In the video he is comparing potatoes with tomatoes. Comparing Co-operatives with the limited companies is preposterous. Cooperatives are made for the people so that they can earn directly from what they are doing without the middleman and its sole purpose is to create more employment through needs of people; whereas the limited company is a private entity, they want to earn profits where there might also be downturns in businesses. He is saying big companies are not hiring. I would ask him to start a company and keep hiring people even if there is no foreseen business or any expansion in site. That's what he has been suggesting in the video. One may listen to a good analysis on a good business channel than watch this nonsense. There are phases for businesses, where currently it is more of less people required. 
Regarding Indian mentality for a Government job, ask any Indian aspiring to get a Government job, 50% just want it for job security, free holiday, Life set karna hai. What's wrong in that? Everything is wrong, people should be aspiring to do the job for the country and not just for Aaram. I have been working with both types of people and have faced them and their mentality. Dhruv bhai do work with them and you would know the "Ground reality". 
Regarding Education, I agree with the part where there needs to be more allocation from the budget and a real push from the Government. Better infra and faculty in Education is the need for the hour. 
BTW, one may notice it very clearly, who he is supporting as a political party from the video. So clear. My fellow Indians, please do your own research for the candidate you are voting for in your area. Just because someone is saying something shouldn't be the deciding factor. Do VOTE but vote for the person who is going to help you in your district/area and do his/her work for the people.

Reality is too deep to be solved.
The basic problem is such that it cannot be solved by any government.
The main problem is the vicious cycle of 3 things:
1. Lack of resources in country
2. Exponential population spurt
3. Poverty
If you deeply understand, even if the professionals are passing out of college, they are not getting the quality of life and standard of living they thought they would get when they entered. Salaries provided by jobs doesnt beat inflation value and stays the same for so many years. Lets understand it with an example.
Assuming a person who has been brought up in a metro city or even a 2nd tyre city becomes a doctor: Even if the government provides job, the location at which he or she will be provided work, is so poorly developed that it will not have the facilities for him/her to live with the same standards which they used to live. Lack of good schools, infrastructure for professional growth and personal systems like theatres, good restaurants, availability of food ultimately making the person unhappy. 
This happened because for a country like India(whose geographic land availability is far less than countries like USA/China but population is tremendous) such population cannot be given the same standard of living which other people have in other countries. Lets understand this with an example.
Lets say there are 2 houses in which 4 Roti are prepared to eat food everyday. One household has 2 members and other has 20 members. Which household will go hungry? So due to this population spurtтАФтАФ Unemployment and poverty has ensued as amount of resources available is far less than that required to support such huge population. On top of this years and years of corruption by so many to fill their pockets has deteriorated this sensitive situation even furthur.
Today if you become a doctor, engineer or any other professional, you pass out from IIT or AIIMS, you are not going to be happy as salaries are not gonna be as per standards, work life is going to be hard, stresses of aging/maturity, change in locations from your own location to distant one due to lack of opportunity and ultimately like this most our lives finish in a hope that India will one day become an economic superpower and all of us will be happy. But reality is far from this belief. 
Most importantly it is not BJP who is responsible for this. It is every single government that came to power and which will come to power since 1947. No one took steps to reduce that one thing that will have improved the long term outcomes of problems of this country: population. And now we have entered a phase of Growth cycle that if we try doing that, we will enter a phase of huge aging population without new youth for the new govt to support. So welcome to reality, even if next 50 years any government comes to power: this situation is never going to resolve. Middle class of India is never going to live the same standard of living a european lives or an american citizen lives.
It mathematically impossible.

*Subject: Urgent Appeal to Safeguard Voting Rights for Agriculture and Non-Agriculture Students in Maharashtra and India*

I am writing to express my deep concern regarding the scheduling of final exams at agricultural universities and non agriculture Universities in Maharashtra and India , which coincides with the general elections, thus depriving thousands of agriculture and allied young students of their fundamental right to vote.

As responsible Indian citizens committed to fostering democratic values and civic engagement, we believe that every individual, irrespective of their academic commitments, should be afforded the opportunity to participate in the electoral process and exercise their right to vote.

The current scheduling of final exams in May presents a significant hurdle to voter participation among agriculture students and other students, many of whom are eager to contribute to the democratic process and nation-building. This denial of voting rights not only undermines democratic principles but also disenfranchises a crucial segment of our population.

Therefore, we urge the Election Commission of India to take immediate action to address this issue and ensure that all eligible voters, including agriculture students and non-agriculture students, have the chance to cast their votes without compromising their academic responsibilities. We recommend exploring alternative exam scheduling arrangements or providing absentee voting options to accommodate students' needs during the election period.

Furthermore, it is imperative to emphasize the importance of raising awareness among young voters about the significance of their participation in elections and the impact of their votes on shaping the nation's future. By actively engaging with young voters and facilitating their involvement in the electoral process, we can strengthen democracy and promote a more inclusive and representative governance system.

In conclusion, we need to appeal the Election Commission of India to prioritize the protection of voting rights for students in Maharashtra and India and to take proactive measures to ensure their full participation in the upcoming elections. We remain steadfast in our commitment to supporting efforts to uphold the integrity of our democratic institutions and safeguard the rights of all citizens.

Concern: Most students are far from their constituencies, making it difficult for them to travel during exam periods.  Given their academic priorities, scheduling exams after or before elections every five years is necessary.

Thank you.
